Project3

Class State

  • java.lang.Object
    • Project3.State

  • public class State
extends java.lang.Object
    1.Create a class named State that will store information about a US state and provide methods to get, and set the data, and compare the states by several fields.

    [X]a. Fields: State Name, Capital City, State Abbreviation, State Population, Region, US House Seats

    [State(String, String, String, int, String, int)]b. Constructor

    [X]c. Get and set methods for each field

    [compareTo(State)]d. Compare method to compare based on State Name (expects a State object as a parameter)

    [printState()]e. Method to print a state

    Version:
    10/24/17
    Author:
    Ryan Geddings N01067534

        public State(java.lang.String paramName,
             java.lang.String paramCapital,
             java.lang.String paramAbbrev,
             int paramPopulation,
             java.lang.String paramRegion,
             int paramSeats)
        Constructor for the state object. Takes in 6 input parameters, 4 of string type, 2 of integer type. These fields are used to maintain data for the State object.
        Parameters:
        paramName - String containing the name of the State in the object
        paramCapital - String containing the Capital of the State in the object
        paramAbbrev - String containing the Abbreviation of the State in the object
        paramPopulation - Integer containing the population of the State in the object
        paramRegion - String containing the region of the State in the object
        paramSeats - Integer containing the number of Seats in the House of the State in the object
